                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Nose Hill Park &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>The community of Edgemont is a direct extension of Nose Hill Park, making it the most significant amenity and landmark of the area.</p>
                    <p>The city's Nose Hill Natural Environment Park is flanked by 12 residential neighbourhoods in the northwest corner. The park was established in 1980 and spans 11 square kilometres. The hill's name comes from the fact that it resembles a nose from certain angles and with some imagination.</p>
                    <p>Some of the features of Nose Hill Park that you can enjoy are:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem">Hiking up the hill and admiring the Rough Fescue grassland you're walking through.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem">One of the most important specimens of this grassland ecosystem on the Canadian prairies may be found in Nose Hill Park. </li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem">Find a wide variety of grasses that are native to the region.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem">Besides the native grasses, the Trembling Aspen is a dominant species in the park. The Aspen, together with the willows, cover the coulees' north-facing slopes.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 2rem">The grasslands and coulees are home to larger animals like deer and coyotes. Porcupines, Richardson's ground squirrels, northern pocket gophers, and a variety of rodents and voles can be found in the park, along with Swainson's hawks.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Some other amenities you can enjoy around Edgemont are shopping at one of the large shopping facilities, such as the Beacon Hill shopping district. You can also enjoy the various sports and fitness activities offered by the Edgemont Community Association.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
