        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>Edgemont is a master-planned neighbourhood that was first established in 1978 by Carma. The neighbourhood took nearly three decades to build, with the last phases finished in 2005.</p>
            <p>Edgemont had a populace of 15,898 people living in 5,421 homes in the 2012 municipal census, down 1.1% from its 2011 demographic of 16,082.</p>
            <p>People in this neighbourhood had an average household income of $88,442 in 2000, according to census data, while 8.6% of residents were considered to be low-income families. Immigrants made up 33.9% of the population in 2000. Condominiums or flats accounted for 5.8% of the structures. While 11.1% of the accommodation was rented, the remaining houses were occupied by their owners.</p>
            <p>Mandarin, Cantonese, Hindi, Urdu, Korean, Punjabi, and French are the most prevalent languages spoken by locals in the community.</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 45.1 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Edgemont has an average of 3 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 49% female and 50% male residents. Approximately 16% of the residents of Edgemont are above the age of 65, compared to 10% for the rest of Calgary.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Edgemont Real Estate includes everything from affordable condominiums and townhouses to luxury homes in the prestigious Edelweiss, Edenstone, and Edgevalley areas. Edgemont's homes, situated high on the mountainside, provide some of Calgary's best city, mountain, and valley views.</p>
            <p>The major housing types in this area of the city are single-family detached homes and townhouses. The majority of the homes in this area of Calgary have three or more bedrooms.</p>
